<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,320,448,474]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[185,315,448,474]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" reason="1">Etymology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species name is a patronym honouring our colleague Stefan H. Foord (Thohoyandou, 
<collectingCountry box="[396,544,483,510]" name="South Africa" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">South Africa</collectingCountry>
), for his contributions to in-depth modern studies of 
<taxonomicName box="[170,296,519,545]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Hersiliidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,335,553,579]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[185,330,553,579]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" reason="1">Description</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Male unknown. Female: Total length 5.01-5.75. Carapace 2.1-2.25 long, 2.2-2.45 wide, femur 3.1-3.75 long, femur I/carapace length ratio 1.47-1.67. Coxae IV separated only slightly. Abdominal pattern such as in 
<typeStatus box="[836,935,624,650]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[968,1108,624,650]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="afghanica">
<emphasis box="[968,1108,624,650]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">H. afghanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
formed by short flat hairs of orange-light brown, dark brown, and white colour.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
Epigyne as in 
<figureCitation box="[356,442,695,721]" captionStart="Figure 13" captionStartId="31.[140,212,1622,1644]" captionTargetBox="[357,895,1225,1600]" captionTargetId="figure@31.[349,898,1218,1605]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="Figure 13. Hersiliola xinjiangenis, after Liang and Wang (1989). 1-2 epigyne, ventral and dorsal, respectively 3-4 male palp, retrolateral and ventral, respectively." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3817424" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3817424/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">Figs 13</figureCitation>
-14, 8.5, with septum as wide as lateral arms of median plate; median plate not well separated from epigynal plate; translucent spermathecae oval, separated by their length (height) from the epigynal opening; insemination duct short, with only one loop; fertilization duct with a long appendix-like accessory gland extending along the duct.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,312,870,896]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[185,307,870,896]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" reason="1">Diagnosis</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[321,497,871,897]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="foordi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[321,497,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">Hersiliola foordi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[506,569,871,897]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
can be easily distinguished from all other congeners by its very short and wide insemination ducts, unseparated median plate, and lack of windows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,324,976,1002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[185,319,976,1002]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" reason="1">Comments</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
This species, like 
<taxonomicName authority="Marusik &amp; Fet, 2009" authorityName="Marusik &amp; Fet" authorityYear="2009" box="[523,656,976,1002]" class="Arachnida" family="Hersiliidae" genus="Hersiliola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindbergi" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[523,656,976,1002]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">H. lindbergi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[663,726,977,1003]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, could belong to a separate genus. Its median plate is not separated from the rest of the epigynal plate. It also has no accessory sclerites and no windows.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="86" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="11.[140,1108,307,1144]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[185,344,1081,1107]" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">
<emphasis box="[185,339,1081,1107]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="86" reason="1">Distribution</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The species is known only from two nearby localities near Shiraz, southern 
<collectingCountry box="[247,297,1118,1144]" name="Iran" pageId="11" pageNumber="86">Iran</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
